If I understand you correctly, you want to compose a multipart request manually from an HTTP/REST console. The multipart format is simple; a brief introduction can be found [in the HTML 4.01 spec][1]. You need to come up with a boundary, which is a string not found in the content, lets say `HereGoes`. You set request header `Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=HereGoes`. Then this should be a valid request body:

